1)Try with resources closes all the resources (file,database connection,network connection etc) 
automatically no need to close them explicitly.This prevents memory leaks

2)With help of try with resource we can reduce unncessary lines of code and makes
the code more readable

************
JAVA 9 allows us to declare resouce outside the Try-With-Resource block.We no longer
need to create local variabel to access the resource.

package com.jay.TryWithResourceEnhancement;

import java.io.FileNotFoundException;
import java.io.FileOutputStream;

public class Example {

	public static void main(String[] args) throws FileNotFoundException {

		FileOutputStream fos = new FileOutputStream("outputfile.txt");
		try(fos){
			fos.write("welcome to jays space".getBytes());
			
		}
		catch(Exception ex)
		{
			ex.printStackTrace();
		}
		
		//no need to use finally block
	}

}
